  schema:name "Murray Bookchin" ;
  schema:description "Murray Bookchin (1921–2006) was an American social theorist who developed social ecology — the analysis that the domination of nature arises from the domination of human by human — and libertarian municipalism, a program for direct democracy through nested federations of popular assemblies." ;
